description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Acute Service Manager&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£45-753-£51,668 (Band 8A)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full time - Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Isle of Wight NHS Trust have an exciting opportunity to work within, and influence the transformation of our Mental Health Acute Care Pathway.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Successful post holder will hold accountability and responsibility for our 6 bedded PICU, 16 bed Adult Acute Ward, the Home Treatment /Liaison Team and the Mental Health Act Management Team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Strong leadership skills and previous management experience will be an asset; the ability to make decisions and show sound, effective communication skills are also required. Previous experience within a mental health inpatient environment is essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Mental Health Services are undergoing wide ranging transformation and as part of this work the successful candidate will be expected to lead the team in review and transformation of the current provision to ensure provision of safe effective and sustainable services.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please contact: Head of Nursing MHLD- Bev Fryer on 01983 822099 ex 4866 for any further details.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
